Someone came to fix the floor in my kitchen, so I'm going to pretend I still have a job and work from home while reviewing Too Hot to Handle.
If I can just open this damn file. (Fucking OneDrive.)
*pirate voice* I'm here.
And that's when it starts drilling really loudly. Great!
His passive-aggressive way of turning up my air purifierannoys me, but it smells like wood chips, so it's justified even if it's an anti-mask. And besides, I really need to protect myself, don't I?
I really want to go back to bed, but I can't until he leaves.
The positive thing is that I finished reading chapter 4!
Chapter five is long, but there's a big cliffhanger. Good work.
Working on find-replace for … ➡️  ellipsis character, and there are 54 of them in this chapter 😅
But anyway, I stick to it. The most natural speeches are usually chopped up, especially when people let themselves be carried away by their emotions.
The craftsman is vacuuming. Fingers crossed, he'll finish soon.
He went out (judging by the sounds) to cut something. So I took a look to see where he was. He's not close to finishing :(<s>
Only 7 pages left for chapter five. It's my favorite chapter, and it's quite well-developed. Some formatting changes and minor adjustments to switch to active voice and improve conciseness. Still, I could use a break and a cup of tea, but the guy is still working in my kitchen.
He just started vacuuming again. I hope that's a good sign.
The craftsman has gone!
Il m'a dit qu'il avait fait un devis pour tout le plancher, mais les propriétaires ont fait les radins et payé juste pour le petit coin abîmé près de la porte. C'est nettement mieux.
La maison s'aère, et mon purificateur d'air tourne dans la cuisine pendant que je profite d'une tasse de thé dans le jardin !
